  "texts": [
    "At the aggregate level, this hypothesis was borne out; the ChatGPT relevance profile of journals agreed with a priori expectations (Table 3).",
    "Likewise, there was a strong nonlinear association between physician and ChatGPT relevance scores at the journal level (standard error of the regression 8.6) (Figure 1).",
    "The standard error of the regression is related to the typical expected prediction error for the regression model.",
    "On our relevance scale, ranging from 0 to 100, a standard error of the regression of 8.6 can therefore be interpreted as an 8.6% expected error in the predicted human-assigned relevance given the ChatGPT-assigned relevance.",
    "Clustering analysis (Figure 2) revealed similarity of the general structure of the clustering dendrograms in both the ChatGPT and human dendrograms."
